data.description:
A magnificent and substantial detached family home constructed to a high specification approximately 4 years ago, by developers of repute, Raybridge Homes, in a highly sought after an convenient location, very close to Roundwood Schools and around a mile from the High Street and station.

This fine house has stylishly presented, well proportioned and versatile accommodation arranged over three floors, featuring a stunning kitchen/family room, beautifully appointed bathroom suites and a generous private garden.

Harpenden is well noted for its excellent choice of schools for all age groups. Sports and social requirements are well catered for, including several challenging golf courses, a sports centre and pool, various clubs and associations and a comprehensive range of restaurants and bars. Harpenden benefits from a fast Thameslink train service to St. Pancras International (c. 26 mintues), the City, Gatwick Airport and beyond to Brighton.

Entrance Via Front Door - 

Entrance Hall - Porcelanosa tiled floors with underfloor heating. Coved ceiling with spotlights. Two double glazed sash windows to side elevation. Door leading into the garage. Stairs to first floor. Storage cupboard, housing CCTV screen and CCTV box recorder (connects to 4 cameras around the house). Alarm control panel.

Living Room - 18'4 into bay x 13' (5.59m into bay x 3.96m) - Accessed via two glass and timber double doors. Porcelanosa tiled floor with underfloor heating. Two double glazed sash windows to side elevation. Double glazed sash bay windows to front elevation. Contemporary gas fire. TV and power points. Corniced ceiling with spotlights. Ceiling music speakers.

Kitchen/Family Room - 23'10 x 19'7 (7.26m x 5.97m) - Beautifully fitted kitchen with large range of base and wall units. Granite work surface with overhang and integral stainless steel sink. Space for range cooker with overhead extractor fan. Teppanyaki hot plate, indoor BBQ, induction hob and further extractor fan overhead. High specification Miele integrated appliances also include dishwasher, microwave oven, fridge, freezer, coffee machine. Ice maker. Porcelanosa tiled floor with underfloor heating. Two double glazed sash windows to both side elevations. Double glazed bi-fold doors to rear elevation stepping out onto patio area. Corniced ceiling with spotlights. TV points. Under stairs storage cupboard.

Play Room/Study - 8'9 x 8'6 (2.67m x 2.59m) - Porcelanosa tiling with underfloor heating. Two double glazed sash windows to rear elevation. Corniced ceiling with spotlights. TV and telephone points.

Utility Room - Butler sink with granite worksurface. Plumbing for washing machine. Obscured double glazed sash window to side elevation. Corniced ceiling with spotlights. Porcelanosa tiled floor with underfloor heating. UPVC doors stepping out to side elevation.

Cloakroom - Concealed cistern WC with granite shelf above. Porcelanosa wall and tiled floor with underfloor heating. Corniced ceiling with spotlights. Vanity cupboard mounted wash hand basin.

Solid oak staircase, leading up to the:

First Floor - 

Landing - Double panel radiator. Airing cupboard with light, housing Megaflow tank and ample shelving.

Master Bedroom - 18'7 x 13' (5.66m x 3.96m) - Two double glazed sash windows to rear elevation. Two double panel radiators. Corniced ceiling with spotlights and built in speakers. Television and telephone points. Emergency alarm point. Hatch access to large loft storage area, (same size as room). Door leading into:

Ensuite - Porcelanosa wall and floor tiles with underfloor heating. Heated towel rail. Jacuzzi bath. Television mounted into the wall. Two frosted double glazed sash windows to rear elevation. Corniced ceiling with spotlights and built in speakers. Low level WC. Vanity cupboard mounted wash hand basin. Shower cubicle.

Dressing Room - Accessed via door from Master bedroom. Fitted wardrobes and drawers with dressing area.

Bedroom Two - 15'3 x 13'11 (4.65m x 4.24m) - Double glazed sash windows to front elevation. Corniced ceiling with spotlights and built in speakers.� TV and telephone points. Built in wardrobes. Double panel radiator. Door into:

En-Suite - Porcelanosa wall and floor tiles with underfloor heating. Shower cubicle. Vanity cupboard mounted wash hand basin set into granite shelf. Frosted double glazed window to side elevation. Concealed cistern WC with granite worksurface and heated towel rail. Built in speaks in ceiling.

Bedroom Three - 11' x 10'10 into bay (3.35m x 3.30m into bay) - Double glazed sash windows to front elevation. Double panel radiator. Cornice ceiling with spotlights and built in speakers. Built in wardrobes. Telephone and television points.

Bedroom Four - 13'10 x 9'9 (4.22m x 2.97m) - Double glazed window to rear elevation. Double panel radiator. Built in wardrobes. Television and telephone points. Corniced ceiling with spotlights and built in speakers. Double panel radiator.

Family Bathroom - Porcelanosa wall and floor tiles with underfloor heating. Large walk in shower with glass screen. Heated towel rail. Frosted double glazed sash window to side elevation. Concealed cistern WC with granite shelf above and a vanity cupboard mounted wash hand basin. Built in speakers.

Stairs Leading Up To The -

Landing - Double panel radiator. Double glazed Velux skylight.

Bedroom Five - 23'7 x 10'9 (7.19m x 3.28m) - Two double glazed Velux skylights. Double panel radiator. Spotlights. Built in wardrobes. Comms cupboard. Door to

Jack And Jill Bathroom - Porcelanosa wall and floor tiles with underfloor heating. Shower cubicle. Spotlights. Double glazed Velux skylight. Vanity cupboard mounted wash hand basin set into granite shelf, concealed cistern WC. Heated towel rail.

Games Room/Gym - 32'3 max x 12'2 max narrowing to 8'3 (9.83m max x - Double panel radiator. Two double glazed Velux skylights and double glazed window to front elevation. Two double panel radiators. Two built in wardrobes. Spotlights. Television and telephone points. Built in speakers. Door to comms cupboard.

Exterior - 

Front Garden - Paved driveway providing off road parking for several vehicles with plant/flower bed.

Garage - 19'9 x 9'4 (6.02m x 2.84m) - Power and lighting, Up and over door. (Please note this garage could easily be converted into another room, subject to the usual building regulations, and could be easily connected to the underfloor heating system, if required.)

Rear Garden - Immediately adjacent to the house is an expanse of paved patio area with the remainder being laid to lawn. Path leading down the side to a rear decked area with large wooden summer house/timber garden studio. Enclosed mainly by panel fencing with brick built wall to the left hand side. Outside power, with exterior lighting and entertainment speakers around the garden.

data.description:
An attractive three bedroom semi detached Victorian house, situated in a popular and highly convenient location, within walking distance of the station and comprehensive town centre amenities. 

The gas centrally heated accommodation includes a bay fronted sitting room and dining area, a kitchen/breakfast room, three bedrooms and a first floor bathroom with separate wc. Outside there is a low maintenance front garden and a good sized rear garden with side access.

Ground Floor - 

Entrance Lobby - Front door. Coved ceiling. Recessed downlight. Glazed door to:

Entrance Hall - Radiator. Staircase to first floor. Coved ceiling. Recessed downlights. Glazed door to dining area.

Sitting/Dining Room - Comprising:

Sitting Area - 14'2 x 10'2 (4.32m x 3.10m) - Measured into bay window to front. Radiator. Oak flooring. Chimney breast with fireplace and fitted shelving to either side. Coved ceiling. Recessed downlights. Open plan to:

Dining Area - 12' x 10'4 (3.66m x 3.15m) - Sash window to rear. Radiator. Oak flooring. Chimney breast with fitted shelves to one side. Under stairs storage cupboard. Coved ceiling. Recessed downlights. Doorway to kitchen/breakfast room.

Kitchen/Breakfast Room - 20'7 x 8'2 (6.27m x 2.49m) - Double glazed window and door to side. Double glazed casement double doors to rear. Fitted with a comprehensive range of wall and base units. Oak block work surfaces incorporating a breakfast bar. Inset one and a half bowl stainless steel sink with mixer tap and drainer. Gas hob with glass splashback and extractor canopy. Fitted oven. Integrated dishwasher. Plumbed for washing machine. Recess for fridge/freezer. Wall mounted cupboard housing gas fired boiler. Oak floor. Radiator. Space for table and chairs. Recessed downlights.

First Floor - 

Landing - Radiator. Coved ceiling. Loft access.

Bedroom One - 12' x 11'3 (3.66m x 3.43m) - Plus depth of custom built fitted wardrobes to one wall. Two double glazed sash windows to front. Radiator. Coved ceiling.

Bedroom Two - 12' x 7'8 (3.66m x 2.34m) - Sash window to rear. Radiator. Chimney breast. Coved ceiling.

Bedroom Three - 9'4 x 8'3 (2.84m x 2.51m) - Double glazed window to rear. Radiator. Cast iron fireplace. Coved ceiling.

Bathroom - Double glazed window to side. Suite comprising bath with mixer tap, wash hand basin and corner shower cubicle. Tiled splash areas. Heated towel rail. Tiled floor. Recessed downlights.

Separate Wc - Low level wc. Tiled floor. Window to side.

Outside - 

Front Garden - Brick boundary wall. Tiled path and area of gravel with shrubs. Side access gate.





Rear Garden - Paved patio. Area of lawn. Various shrubs. Timber garden shed. Outside tap.
